data.text:
Music my dad loved plus Linda Ronstadt, Los Lobos, Richie Valens, Carlos Santana, Freddy Fender and the Texas Tornadoes.

Tonight on LA Sounds it would be my father’s birthday so to honor my father I’ll be playing music I grew up listening to my dad playing and singing by artists such as Al Jolson, Bessie Smith, Billie Holiday, Eddie Cantor, the Ink Spots and Louie Prima as well as music I listened to in East LA where I grew up by Linda Ronstadt, Los Lobos, Richie Valens, Carlos Santana, Freddy Fender and the Texas Tornadoes.
